# COBOL Codebase Reverse Engineering Plan

## Milestones

### V1: Initial Slice (Proof of Concept)
- [ ] Assess the codebase and identify a small, representative slice of the rules to reverse engineer.
- [ ] Create Human-Readable Rule Book for the slice.
- [ ] Create Machine-Readable Rule Artifacts for the slice.
- [ ] Create System Architecture Documentation (UML/Sequence) for the slice.
- [ ] Create Rule to Manual Linkage for the slice.
- [ ] Run acceptance testing / review with USER.

### V2: Expanded Slice
- [ ] Expand the slice to cover a more complete set of related rules.
- [ ] Update Human-Readable Rule Book.
- [ ] Update Machine-Readable Rule Artifacts.
- [ ] Update System Architecture Documentation.
- [ ] Update Rule to Manual Linkage.
- [ ] Run acceptance testing / review with USER.

### V3: Complete Set
- [ ] Expand to the remaining rules in the codebase.
- [ ] Finalize Human-Readable Rule Book.
- [ ] Finalize Machine-Readable Rule Artifacts.
- [ ] Finalize System Architecture Documentation.
- [ ] Finalize Rule to Manual Linkage.
- [ ] Final acceptance testing / review.
